## The Whole Thing

Everything from notebooks 16-18 — RoPE, RMSNorm, GQA, QK norm, sliding window, ReLU-squared, value embeddings, residual scaling, softcapping — fits in **one file, 292 lines**. Open `lib/ex_nano_gpt/v2_compact.ex` and read it top to bottom.

```elixir
Code.require_file("../lib/ex_nano_gpt/v2_compact.ex")

# Run the compact model
compact_logits = ExNanoGPT.V2Compact.forward(idx, params, config)

diff =
  Nx.subtract(compact_logits, logits)
  |> Nx.abs()
  |> Nx.reduce_max()
  |> Nx.to_number()

IO.puts("Max diff between reference and v2_compact.ex: #{diff}")
IO.puts(if diff < 1.0e-4, do: "✓ Identical. You just built this 292-line model piece by piece.", else: "✗ Mismatch — #{diff}")
```

<details>
<summary>The entire forward pass from v2_compact.ex</summary>

```elixir
# lib/ex_nano_gpt/v2_compact.ex — forward/3
def forward(idx, params, %__MODULE__{} = config) do
  %{n_layer: n, n_head: nh, n_kv_head: nkv, n_embd: d} = config
  head_dim = div(d, nh)
  seq_len = Nx.axis_size(idx, 1)
  ws = window_sizes(config)
  {cos, sin} = precompute_rope(seq_len, head_dim)

  x = Nx.take(params.wte, idx, axis: 0) |> rms_norm()
  x0 = x

  x =
    Enum.reduce(0..(n - 1), x, fn i, x ->
      rl = Nx.reshape(params.resid_lambdas[i], {1, 1, 1})
      xl = Nx.reshape(params.x0_lambdas[i], {1, 1, 1})
      x = Nx.add(Nx.multiply(rl, x), Nx.multiply(xl, x0))

      block(x, elem(params.blocks, i), elem(params.value_embeds, i), idx, cos, sin,
        n_head: nh, n_kv_head: nkv, window_size: Enum.at(ws, i))
    end)

  logits = Nx.dot(rms_norm(x), [-1], params.lm_head, [1])
  Nx.multiply(@softcap, Nx.tanh(Nx.divide(logits, @softcap)))
end
```

RoPE frequencies, RMSNorm, per-layer residual scaling with x0 skip, value embeddings, sliding window attention, softcapping. Every line maps to something you built and verified in notebooks 16-18.

</details>

## What's Next

The model is built. But it only works with character-level tokens — one byte per character. Next: **BPE tokenization**, the algorithm that went from a 1994 data compression paper to the foundation of every modern LLM's vocabulary.

## Key Concepts

| Concept | What it means |
|---------|--------------|
| **ReLU-squared** | `max(0, x)²` — sparser than GELU, better feature selection. Zhang et al., Feb 2024. |
| **Softcapping** | `c · tanh(logits/c)` — smooth logit bounding. Gemma 2 team, Google 2024. |
| **Value embeddings** | Token-identity signals added to V on alternating layers. From nGPT / nanochat. |
| **Residual scaling** | `λ_r · x + λ_0 · x₀` — per-layer gradient highways |
| **Untied embeddings** | Separate input (wte) and output (lm_head) weight matrices |
